{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/migrating-a-wordpress-site-to-a-live-server/","webpackCompilationHash":"","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you already know <a href=\"http://taniarascia.com/local-environment\">how to set up a local server</a> and get WordPress up and running, migrating to a live server is extremely simple. We'll avoid the dreaded \"Error establishing a database connection\" once and for all.</p>\n<h4 id=\"prerequisites\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\" aria-label=\"prerequisites permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>A local WordPress install</li>\n<li>A web server that supports PHP and MySQL</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"goal\"><a href=\"#goal\" aria-label=\"goal permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Goal</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Migrate WordPress from a local to live server</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note that this tutorial doesn't cover all use cases, but is a foundation for transferring a simple website. Certain plugins and functions might require more specific migration steps, which can be found <a href=\"https://codex.wordpress.org/Moving_WordPress\">in the WordPress codex</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"migrating-wordpress\"><a href=\"#migrating-wordpress\" aria-label=\"migrating wordpress permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Migrating WordPress</h2>\n<p>So, you already have a WordPress site set up, and you just want to push it to your server. You can do this through <a href=\"http://www.taniarascia.com/getting-started-with-git/\">Git and SSH</a>, but for the sake of simplicity I'm just going to use <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File_Transfer_Protocol\">(S)FTP</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"export-your-database-to-the-live-server\"><a href=\"#export-your-database-to-the-live-server\" aria-label=\"export your database to the live server permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Export your database to the live server</h3>\n<p>You may have been using phpMyAdmin in MAMP for your database needs. You could also be using a program such as <a href=\"http://www.sequelpro.com/\">SequelPro</a> for Mac, or <a href=\"https://www.webyog.com/\">SQLYog</a> on Windows. Chances are, your host has phpMyAdmin access, or a similar open source GUI, so I would recommend using that to start.</p>\n<p>Open phpMyAdmin in MAMP, and click on the database you have WordPress installed in. Mine was <strong>startwordpress</strong>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 850px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b768ac61f3366f790bf26b8236df84da/9b869/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.19.23-PM.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 36.92838654012079%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 19 23 PM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 19 23 PM\"\n        src=\"/static/b768ac61f3366f790bf26b8236df84da/4d3f1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.19.23-PM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b768ac61f3366f790bf26b8236df84da/0cb30/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.19.23-PM.png 213w,\n/static/b768ac61f3366f790bf26b8236df84da/a67b6/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.19.23-PM.png 425w,\n/static/b768ac61f3366f790bf26b8236df84da/4d3f1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.19.23-PM.png 850w,\n/static/b768ac61f3366f790bf26b8236df84da/9b869/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.19.23-PM.png 1159w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Click on the _options table. Your prefix may vary. The default is <code class=\"language-text\">wp_options</code>, but in my case it's <code class=\"language-text\">xyz_options</code>.</p>\n<p>At the top, click on <strong>Browse</strong>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 850px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1bc64241ab10074e2efcbaec45fa325d/6a03e/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.27.25-PM.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.41067285382831%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 27 25 PM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 27 25 PM\"\n        src=\"/static/1bc64241ab10074e2efcbaec45fa325d/4d3f1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.27.25-PM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1bc64241ab10074e2efcbaec45fa325d/0cb30/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.27.25-PM.png 213w,\n/static/1bc64241ab10074e2efcbaec45fa325d/a67b6/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.27.25-PM.png 425w,\n/static/1bc64241ab10074e2efcbaec45fa325d/4d3f1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.27.25-PM.png 850w,\n/static/1bc64241ab10074e2efcbaec45fa325d/6a03e/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.27.25-PM.png 862w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You will need to change two rows in the table - <strong>siteurl</strong> and <strong>home</strong>. Sometimes they're right next to each other, and sometimes you have to look for them. In this case, they're conveniently located right next to each other.</p>\n<p>I had my URL set to <strong><a href=\"http://startwordpress.dev\">http://startwordpress.dev</a></strong> while I was working on it in MAMP. Now I'll point it at my server, <strong><a href=\"http://example.com\">http://example.com</a></strong>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 779px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2a26e348dfe317bdbf58809f82c570e1/16fa1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.31.36-PM.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 9.114249037227214%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAACCAYAAABYBvyLAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAiElEQVQI1w3J3RJCQACAUe//RClTk8H4jcYqdmd3RUh6hy8X5+o4yk60eqaRE7qfadVI3S4kxQ/RLfu9ifON9LbxUCtmnOnsi7yaCOKF4v6lnxek/eBHK04WP0kTyfkiqdOW66GjrEaGQVFVJUEQYozEWrXTCCFw3SOedyIK/f0UWhuaRlCWGX+z2YwSeS06QQAAAABJRU5ErkJggg=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 31 36 PM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 31 36 PM\"\n        src=\"/static/2a26e348dfe317bdbf58809f82c570e1/16fa1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.31.36-PM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2a26e348dfe317bdbf58809f82c570e1/0cb30/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.31.36-PM.png 213w,\n/static/2a26e348dfe317bdbf58809f82c570e1/a67b6/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.31.36-PM.png 425w,\n/static/2a26e348dfe317bdbf58809f82c570e1/16fa1/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.31.36-PM.png 779w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 779px) 100vw, 779px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Your local site will no longer work at this point. You can change the values back and it will work again. Now that that's set, go back to your database and click <strong>Export</strong> at the top. Select <strong>Custom</strong>, <strong>Save output to a file</strong>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note that if your server is running an old version of MySQL, you might have to change \"Database system or older MySQL server to maximize output compatibility with:\" and set NONE to MYSQL40.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 659px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/438e2d9c65e396a3218ca807fc7a8eb4/f4d47/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.42.40-PM.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100.15174506828528%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 42 40 PM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 42 40 PM\"\n        src=\"/static/438e2d9c65e396a3218ca807fc7a8eb4/f4d47/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.42.40-PM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/438e2d9c65e396a3218ca807fc7a8eb4/0cb30/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.42.40-PM.png 213w,\n/static/438e2d9c65e396a3218ca807fc7a8eb4/a67b6/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.42.40-PM.png 425w,\n/static/438e2d9c65e396a3218ca807fc7a8eb4/f4d47/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.42.40-PM.png 659w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 659px) 100vw, 659px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Select <strong>Go</strong> at the bottom, and <strong>yourdatabase.sql</strong> will download.</p>\n<h3 id=\"import-your-database-to-the-live-server\"><a href=\"#import-your-database-to-the-live-server\" aria-label=\"import your database to the live server permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Import your database to the live server</h3>\n<p>Find phpMyAdmin in your server. It should look basically the same as the MAMP version. Create a new database, and this time you're going to choose <strong>Import</strong>. Choose file and import <strong>yourdatabase.sql</strong>.</p>\n<p>Where your server lists the information for FTP, it will also list your user and password for MySQL. You need a user to connect to MySQL, so make sure to find this information. If you haven't created a user before, find out where to do this and create one.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 530px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a5fba0841a36fa1000bc791a046d3eb2/3e6fd/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.55.28-PM.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.471698113207545%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 55 28 PM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2015 10 22 at 9 55 28 PM\"\n        src=\"/static/a5fba0841a36fa1000bc791a046d3eb2/3e6fd/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.55.28-PM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a5fba0841a36fa1000bc791a046d3eb2/0cb30/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.55.28-PM.png 213w,\n/static/a5fba0841a36fa1000bc791a046d3eb2/a67b6/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.55.28-PM.png 425w,\n/static/a5fba0841a36fa1000bc791a046d3eb2/3e6fd/Screen-Shot-2015-10-22-at-9.55.28-PM.png 530w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 530px) 100vw, 530px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"upload-your-files-to-the-server\"><a href=\"#upload-your-files-to-the-server\" aria-label=\"upload your files to the server permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Upload your files to the server</h3>\n<p>This one is easy if you've ever uploaded any sort of file to a server. You'll just use a program like <a href=\"https://filezilla-project.org/\">FileZilla</a> or <a href=\"https://panic.com/transmit/\">Transmit</a>. Copy all the files over to the directory you want it to show up in. Usually it's called public on a web server.</p>\n<h3 id=\"change-your-wordpress-configuration\"><a href=\"#change-your-wordpress-configuration\" aria-label=\"change your wordpress configuration permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Change your WordPress configuration.</h3>\n<p>Before, you created a file called <strong>wp-config.php</strong> in the root of the WordPress install. For your local version, it looked like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"token comment\">/** The name of the database for WordPress */</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">define</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'DB_NAME'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'startwordpress'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/** MySQL database username */</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">define</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'DB_USER'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'root'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/** MySQL database password */</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">define</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'DB_PASSWORD'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'root'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>On your live server, change these three options to match your live server database, user and password.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"token comment\">/** The name of the database for WordPress */</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">define</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'DB_NAME'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'startwordpress'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/** MySQL database username */</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">define</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'DB_USER'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'dbusername'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/** MySQL database password */</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">define</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'DB_PASSWORD'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'dbpassword'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">define(&#39;DB_HOST&#39;, &#39;localhost&#39;);</code> will most likely remain the same, but some hosts create a different host for databases.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Now if you go to your URL, it should all be loading properly! Load the WordPress backend, click <strong>Settings > Permalinks</strong> and update permalinks.</p>\n<h3 id=\"update-permissions\"><a href=\"#update-permissions\" aria-label=\"update permissions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Update permissions</h3>\n<p>In FTP, migrate to your <strong>wp-uploads</strong> folder, and change the permissions to \"666\". This will allow you to upload media.</p>\n<h3 id=\"find-and-replace-urls-in-database\"><a href=\"#find-and-replace-urls-in-database\" aria-label=\"find and replace urls in database permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Find and replace URLs in database</h3>\n<p>If you have some posts where you refer to links by URL, you might have to change them. The <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/better-search-replace/\">Better Search Replace</a> plugin is a wonderful tool that allows you to search your entire database for instances of a \"string\", and replace them.</p>\n<p>Be sure to backup your database before applying any changes.</p>","timeToRead":5,"excerpt":"If you already know how to set up a local server and get WordPress up and running, migrating to a live server is extremely simple. We'llâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Migrating a WordPress Site to a Live Server","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":150,"height":150,"src":"/static/6fbbc005662821ae7cc14e2ccb765c40/4148e/wp.png","srcSet":"/static/6fbbc005662821ae7cc14e2ccb765c40/4148e/wp.png 1x"}}},"slug":"migrating-a-wordpress-site-to-a-live-server","date":"2015-10-23T00:00:00.000Z","categories":["Code"],"tags":["php","wordpress"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/migrating-a-wordpress-site-to-a-live-server/","date":"2015-10-23T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/migrating-a-wordpress-site-to-a-live-server/"}}}